Transform a dict of the form
{'a.b.c': value1, 'a.b.d': value2, 'z': value3}
into
{'a': {'b': {'c': value1, 'd': value2}}, 'z': value3}

On incompatible input keys (for example: 'a.b.c', 'a', 'a.d'), the last key wins

